{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ScNSxQSSxQXMxWcHpDv5Tn","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"logical fallacy detection dataset benchmark NLP HuggingFace\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"tasksource/logical-fallacy · Datasets at Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/tasksource/logical-fallacy\"},{\"title\":\"brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies · Datasets at Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies\"},{\"title\":\"Paper page - CoCoLoFa: A Dataset of News Comments with Common Logical Fallacies Written by LLM-Assisted Crowds\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/papers/2410.03457\"},{\"title\":\"[2202.13758] Logical Fallacy Detection\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2202.13758\"},{\"title\":\"MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base · Datasets at Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base\"},{\"title\":\"Paper page - Logical Fallacy Detection\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/papers/2202.13758\"},{\"title\":\"q3fer/distilbert-base-fallacy-classification · Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/q3fer/distilbert-base-fallacy-classification\"},{\"title\":\"MidhunKanadan/logical-fallacy-classification · Datasets at Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/MidhunKanadan/logical-fallacy-classification\"},{\"title\":\"benmshultz/RuFal_fallacy_detection · Datasets at Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/benmshultz/RuFal_fallacy_detection\"},{\"title\":\"joey234/mmlu-logical_fallacies-original-neg · Datasets at Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/joey234/mmlu-logical_fallacies-original-neg\"}]\n\nHere are the key findings on **logical fallacy detection datasets and benchmarks** available on HuggingFace and in the NLP community:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **tasksource/logical-fallacy** (Primary Benchmark)\nThis dataset contains approximately 3,760 rows, split into train (2,680 rows), test (511 rows), and dev (570 rows). It is based on the foundational paper by Jin, Zhijing et al. (2022), \"Logical Fallacy Detection,\" published as arXiv preprint arXiv:2202.13758. This is widely considered the go-to benchmark for this task.\n\n### 2. **Key Paper: Logical Fallacy Detection (Jin et al., 2022)**\nThe authors found that existing pretrained large language models perform poorly on this task. In contrast, a simple structure-aware classifier outperformed the best language model by 5.46% on Logic and 4.51% on LogicClimate.\n\n### 3. **CoCoLoFa Dataset (2024)**\nBERT-based models fine-tuned using CoCoLoFa achieved the highest fallacy detection (F1=0.86) and classification (F1=0.87) performance on its test set, outperforming state-of-the-art LLMs.\n\n### 4. **q3fer/distilbert-base-fallacy-classification** (Fine-tuned Model)\nThis model is a fine-tuned version of distilbert-base-uncased on the Logical Fallacy Dataset, fine-tuned for text classification of logical fallacies. There are a total of 14 classes: ad hominem, ad populum, appeal to emotion, circular reasoning, equivocation, fallacy of credibility, fallacy of extension, fallacy of logic, fallacy of relevance, false causality, false dilemma, faulty generalization, intentional, and miscellaneous.\n\n### 5. **MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base**\nThis dataset was produced for the purpose of enabling more accurate detection and handling of logical and other fallacies in LLMs. Seed data was taken from Wikipedia's list of Fallacies, and rows were produced synthetically with Gemini 1.5 Flash, Experimental, and Pro over the Vertex AI Google Cloud UI.\n\n### 6. **MidhunKanadan/logical-fallacy-classification**\nThis dataset is intended for the classification of logical fallacies in text and is useful for training and evaluating models that aim to detect and categorize various types of logical fallacies.\n\n### 7. **benmshultz/RuFal_fallacy_detection**\nThis dataset contains 700 annotated Russian government tweets, labelled with 13 logical fallacy types, as proposed in the novel Logical Fallacy Detection task (Jin et al.).\n\n### 8. **MMLU-based Fallacy Datasets**\nThere are also MMLU-derived logical fallacy subsets available, such as `brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies` and `joey234/mmlu-logical_fallacies-original-neg`.\n\n---\n\n**Summary:** The most established benchmark is the **Jin et al. (2022) Logical Fallacy Detection dataset** (`tasksource/logical-fallacy`), with 14 fallacy categories and ~3.7K examples. For state-of-the-art results, the **CoCoLoFa** dataset has shown strong performance with BERT-based fine-tuning. Multiple fine-tuned models and derivative datasets are also available on HuggingFace.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"607fdfc9-907f-4bc3-829a-6743699977ac","uuid":"a57b6426-54f7-4735-a61d-1e04c5521b50","tool_use_result":{"query":"logical fallacy detection dataset benchmark NLP HuggingFace","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01CSysAspGLFz6n99FCvh1GD","content":[{"title":"tasksource/logical-fallacy · Datasets at Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/datasets/tasksource/logical-fallacy"},{"title":"brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies · Datasets at Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/datasets/brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies"},{"title":"Paper page - CoCoLoFa: A Dataset of News Comments with Common Logical Fallacies Written by LLM-Assisted Crowds","url":"https://huggingface.co/papers/2410.03457"},{"title":"[2202.13758] Logical Fallacy Detection","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2202.13758"},{"title":"MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base · Datasets at Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/datasets/MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base"},{"title":"Paper page - Logical Fallacy Detection","url":"https://huggingface.co/papers/2202.13758"},{"title":"q3fer/distilbert-base-fallacy-classification · Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/q3fer/distilbert-base-fallacy-classification"},{"title":"MidhunKanadan/logical-fallacy-classification · Datasets at Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/datasets/MidhunKanadan/logical-fallacy-classification"},{"title":"benmshultz/RuFal_fallacy_detection · Datasets at Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/datasets/benmshultz/RuFal_fallacy_detection"},{"title":"joey234/mmlu-logical_fallacies-original-neg · Datasets at Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/datasets/joey234/mmlu-logical_fallacies-original-neg"}]},"Here are the key findings on **logical fallacy detection datasets and benchmarks** available on HuggingFace and in the NLP community:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **tasksource/logical-fallacy** (Primary Benchmark)\nThis dataset contains approximately 3,760 rows, split into train (2,680 rows), test (511 rows), and dev (570 rows). It is based on the foundational paper by Jin, Zhijing et al. (2022), \"Logical Fallacy Detection,\" published as arXiv preprint arXiv:2202.13758. This is widely considered the go-to benchmark for this task.\n\n### 2. **Key Paper: Logical Fallacy Detection (Jin et al., 2022)**\nThe authors found that existing pretrained large language models perform poorly on this task. In contrast, a simple structure-aware classifier outperformed the best language model by 5.46% on Logic and 4.51% on LogicClimate.\n\n### 3. **CoCoLoFa Dataset (2024)**\nBERT-based models fine-tuned using CoCoLoFa achieved the highest fallacy detection (F1=0.86) and classification (F1=0.87) performance on its test set, outperforming state-of-the-art LLMs.\n\n### 4. **q3fer/distilbert-base-fallacy-classification** (Fine-tuned Model)\nThis model is a fine-tuned version of distilbert-base-uncased on the Logical Fallacy Dataset, fine-tuned for text classification of logical fallacies. There are a total of 14 classes: ad hominem, ad populum, appeal to emotion, circular reasoning, equivocation, fallacy of credibility, fallacy of extension, fallacy of logic, fallacy of relevance, false causality, false dilemma, faulty generalization, intentional, and miscellaneous.\n\n### 5. **MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base**\nThis dataset was produced for the purpose of enabling more accurate detection and handling of logical and other fallacies in LLMs. Seed data was taken from Wikipedia's list of Fallacies, and rows were produced synthetically with Gemini 1.5 Flash, Experimental, and Pro over the Vertex AI Google Cloud UI.\n\n### 6. **MidhunKanadan/logical-fallacy-classification**\nThis dataset is intended for the classification of logical fallacies in text and is useful for training and evaluating models that aim to detect and categorize various types of logical fallacies.\n\n### 7. **benmshultz/RuFal_fallacy_detection**\nThis dataset contains 700 annotated Russian government tweets, labelled with 13 logical fallacy types, as proposed in the novel Logical Fallacy Detection task (Jin et al.).\n\n### 8. **MMLU-based Fallacy Datasets**\nThere are also MMLU-derived logical fallacy subsets available, such as `brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies` and `joey234/mmlu-logical_fallacies-original-neg`.\n\n---\n\n**Summary:** The most established benchmark is the **Jin et al. (2022) Logical Fallacy Detection dataset** (`tasksource/logical-fallacy`), with 14 fallacy categories and ~3.7K examples. For state-of-the-art results, the **CoCoLoFa** dataset has shown strong performance with BERT-based fine-tuning. Multiple fine-tuned models and derivative datasets are also available on HuggingFace."],"durationSeconds":25.01685555400001}}
