{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NgpDAAjgKUBews2LNWDhhN","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"github logical fallacy detection LLM evaluation code repository\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"GitHub - causalNLP/logical-fallacy: Repo for the paper \\\"Detecting Logical Fallacies: From Quiz to Climate Change News\\\" (2021)\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/causalNLP/logical-fallacy\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - alopatenko/LLMEvaluation: A comprehensive guide to LLM evaluation methods designed to assist in identifying the most suitable evaluation techniques for various use cases, promote the adoption of best practices in LLM assessment, and critically assess the effectiveness of these evaluation methods. · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/alopatenko/LLMEvaluation\"},{\"title\":\"RuozhiBench: Evaluating LLMs with Logical Fallacies and Misleading Premises\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2502.13125v1\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - tmakesense/logical-fallacy: Logical fallacy online detection tools\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/tmakesense/logical-fallacy\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - jingwora/LLM-Evaluation\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/jingwora/LLM-Evaluation\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - usc-isi-i2/logical-fallacy-identification\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/usc-isi-i2/logical-fallacy-identification\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - SeanFlannery/Logical.ly: Automated Logical Fallacy Detection (Purdue CS 577 NLP Final Project)\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/SeanFlannery/Logical.ly\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - codefuse-ai/Awesome-Code-LLM: [TMLR] A curated list of language modeling researches for code (and other software engineering activities), plus related datasets. · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/codefuse-ai/Awesome-Code-LLM\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - pierpaologoffredo/FallacyDetection: This is the repository for the task of Fallacy Detection\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/pierpaologoffredo/FallacyDetection\"},{\"title\":\"fallacies · GitHub Topics\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/topics/fallacies\"}]\n\nHere are the most relevant GitHub repositories found related to **logical fallacy detection**, **LLM evaluation**, and related code:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **[causalNLP/logical-fallacy](https://github.com/causalNLP/logical-fallacy)**\nThis is the repo for the paper \"Logical Fallacy Detection\" (Findings of EMNLP 2022) by Abhinav Lalwani, Zhijing Jin, Tejas Vaidhya, Xiaoyu Shen, and others. They propose the task of logical fallacy detection and provide a new dataset (Logic) of logical fallacies generally found in text, together with an additional challenge set for detecting logical fallacies in climate change claims (LogicClimate). They find that existing pretrained large language models perform poorly on this task, and show that a simple structure-aware classifier outperforms the best language model by 5.46% F1 scores on Logic and 4.51% on LogicClimate.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **[LibrAIResearch/ruozhibench](https://github.com/LibrAIResearch/ruozhibench)**\nRuozhiBench is a bilingual dataset comprising 677 carefully curated questions that contain various forms of deceptive reasoning, meticulously crafted through extensive human effort and expert review. In a comprehensive evaluation of 17 LLMs from 5 series, models showed limited ability to detect and reason correctly about logical fallacies, with even the best-performing model, Claude-3-haiku, achieving only 62% accuracy compared to the human upper bound of more than 90%.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **[tmakesense/logical-fallacy](https://github.com/tmakesense/logical-fallacy)**\nThis project provides logical fallacy online detection tools, with a list of detectable fallacies available on their website. It includes an Android App Logical Fallacy Detector and Twitter bots that detect logical fallacies in tweets. It also contains the original repo and dataset with annotated examples of logical fallacies for training ML models.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **[usc-isi-i2/logical-fallacy-identification](https://github.com/usc-isi-i2/logical-fallacy-identification)**\nThis repository contains scripts and associated notebooks with experiments performed on different modules associated with the project on Logical Fallacy Identification. It includes codebases for AMR parsers and graphs, data augmentation, fallacy classification, propaganda detection, and prototype-based learning (Prototex).\n\n---\n\n### 5. **[pierpaologoffredo/FallacyDetection](https://github.com/pierpaologoffredo/FallacyDetection)**\nThis repository contains code for the experiments in the paper \"Argument-based Detection and Classification of Fallacies in Political Debates\" (EMNLP 2023), addressing the task of detecting and classifying fallacious arguments in political debates. It introduces MultiFusion BERT, a novel neural architecture for fallacious argument detection and classification, combining text, argumentative features, and engineered features.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **[SeanFlannery/Logical.ly](https://github.com/SeanFlannery/Logical.ly)**\nThis is a Purdue CS 577 NLP final project that found a suitable corpus for scraping examples of logical fallacies, noting substantial recent interest in automated fallacy detection both in online forums and in formal engineering specifications.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **[alopatenko/LLMEvaluation](https://github.com/alopatenko/LLMEvaluation)**\nA comprehensive guide to LLM evaluation methods designed to assist in identifying the most suitable evaluation techniques for various use cases, promote the adoption of best practices in LLM assessment, and critically assess the effectiveness of these evaluation methods. This includes references to logical reasoning benchmarks and evaluation frameworks.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **[jingwora/LLM-Evaluation](https://github.com/jingwora/LLM-Evaluation)**\nLLM-Evaluation is a collection of tools and techniques designed to assess the performance and capabilities of LLMs, providing a comprehensive suite for evaluating various aspects including accuracy, efficiency, robustness, and adaptability, with automated benchmarking scripts, detailed metric reports, and comparison utilities.\n\n---\n\nThese repositories span from dedicated logical fallacy detection datasets and classifiers to broader LLM evaluation frameworks that include reasoning and logic assessments.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"607fdfc9-907f-4bc3-829a-6743699977ac","uuid":"382d011b-1716-4390-886d-51d8ed08bb97","tool_use_result":{"query":"github logical fallacy detection LLM evaluation code repository","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01XR5EPyERJ5h8KFjm1LbUTQ","content":[{"title":"GitHub - causalNLP/logical-fallacy: Repo for the paper \"Detecting Logical Fallacies: From Quiz to Climate Change News\" (2021)","url":"https://github.com/causalNLP/logical-fallacy"},{"title":"GitHub - alopatenko/LLMEvaluation: A comprehensive guide to LLM evaluation methods designed to assist in identifying the most suitable evaluation techniques for various use cases, promote the adoption of best practices in LLM assessment, and critically assess the effectiveness of these evaluation methods. · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/alopatenko/LLMEvaluation"},{"title":"RuozhiBench: Evaluating LLMs with Logical Fallacies and Misleading Premises","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2502.13125v1"},{"title":"GitHub - tmakesense/logical-fallacy: Logical fallacy online detection tools","url":"https://github.com/tmakesense/logical-fallacy"},{"title":"GitHub - jingwora/LLM-Evaluation","url":"https://github.com/jingwora/LLM-Evaluation"},{"title":"GitHub - usc-isi-i2/logical-fallacy-identification","url":"https://github.com/usc-isi-i2/logical-fallacy-identification"},{"title":"GitHub - SeanFlannery/Logical.ly: Automated Logical Fallacy Detection (Purdue CS 577 NLP Final Project)","url":"https://github.com/SeanFlannery/Logical.ly"},{"title":"GitHub - codefuse-ai/Awesome-Code-LLM: [TMLR] A curated list of language modeling researches for code (and other software engineering activities), plus related datasets. · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/codefuse-ai/Awesome-Code-LLM"},{"title":"GitHub - pierpaologoffredo/FallacyDetection: This is the repository for the task of Fallacy Detection","url":"https://github.com/pierpaologoffredo/FallacyDetection"},{"title":"fallacies · GitHub Topics","url":"https://github.com/topics/fallacies"}]},"Here are the most relevant GitHub repositories found related to **logical fallacy detection**, **LLM evaluation**, and related code:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **[causalNLP/logical-fallacy](https://github.com/causalNLP/logical-fallacy)**\nThis is the repo for the paper \"Logical Fallacy Detection\" (Findings of EMNLP 2022) by Abhinav Lalwani, Zhijing Jin, Tejas Vaidhya, Xiaoyu Shen, and others. They propose the task of logical fallacy detection and provide a new dataset (Logic) of logical fallacies generally found in text, together with an additional challenge set for detecting logical fallacies in climate change claims (LogicClimate). They find that existing pretrained large language models perform poorly on this task, and show that a simple structure-aware classifier outperforms the best language model by 5.46% F1 scores on Logic and 4.51% on LogicClimate.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **[LibrAIResearch/ruozhibench](https://github.com/LibrAIResearch/ruozhibench)**\nRuozhiBench is a bilingual dataset comprising 677 carefully curated questions that contain various forms of deceptive reasoning, meticulously crafted through extensive human effort and expert review. In a comprehensive evaluation of 17 LLMs from 5 series, models showed limited ability to detect and reason correctly about logical fallacies, with even the best-performing model, Claude-3-haiku, achieving only 62% accuracy compared to the human upper bound of more than 90%.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **[tmakesense/logical-fallacy](https://github.com/tmakesense/logical-fallacy)**\nThis project provides logical fallacy online detection tools, with a list of detectable fallacies available on their website. It includes an Android App Logical Fallacy Detector and Twitter bots that detect logical fallacies in tweets. It also contains the original repo and dataset with annotated examples of logical fallacies for training ML models.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **[usc-isi-i2/logical-fallacy-identification](https://github.com/usc-isi-i2/logical-fallacy-identification)**\nThis repository contains scripts and associated notebooks with experiments performed on different modules associated with the project on Logical Fallacy Identification. It includes codebases for AMR parsers and graphs, data augmentation, fallacy classification, propaganda detection, and prototype-based learning (Prototex).\n\n---\n\n### 5. **[pierpaologoffredo/FallacyDetection](https://github.com/pierpaologoffredo/FallacyDetection)**\nThis repository contains code for the experiments in the paper \"Argument-based Detection and Classification of Fallacies in Political Debates\" (EMNLP 2023), addressing the task of detecting and classifying fallacious arguments in political debates. It introduces MultiFusion BERT, a novel neural architecture for fallacious argument detection and classification, combining text, argumentative features, and engineered features.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **[SeanFlannery/Logical.ly](https://github.com/SeanFlannery/Logical.ly)**\nThis is a Purdue CS 577 NLP final project that found a suitable corpus for scraping examples of logical fallacies, noting substantial recent interest in automated fallacy detection both in online forums and in formal engineering specifications.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **[alopatenko/LLMEvaluation](https://github.com/alopatenko/LLMEvaluation)**\nA comprehensive guide to LLM evaluation methods designed to assist in identifying the most suitable evaluation techniques for various use cases, promote the adoption of best practices in LLM assessment, and critically assess the effectiveness of these evaluation methods. This includes references to logical reasoning benchmarks and evaluation frameworks.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **[jingwora/LLM-Evaluation](https://github.com/jingwora/LLM-Evaluation)**\nLLM-Evaluation is a collection of tools and techniques designed to assess the performance and capabilities of LLMs, providing a comprehensive suite for evaluating various aspects including accuracy, efficiency, robustness, and adaptability, with automated benchmarking scripts, detailed metric reports, and comparison utilities.\n\n---\n\nThese repositories span from dedicated logical fallacy detection datasets and classifiers to broader LLM evaluation frameworks that include reasoning and logic assessments."],"durationSeconds":31.224085021000008}}
