{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HC8MtE6rLvCTivND2ufhJu","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"CoCoLoFa dataset download github huggingface logical fallacies\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"GitHub - Crowd-AI-Lab/cocolofa\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/Crowd-AI-Lab/cocolofa\"},{\"title\":\"tasksource/logical-fallacy · Datasets at Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/tasksource/logical-fallacy\"},{\"title\":\"Paper page - CoCoLoFa: A Dataset of News Comments with Common Logical Fallacies Written by LLM-Assisted Crowds\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/papers/2410.03457\"},{\"title\":\"brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies · Datasets at Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies\"},{\"title\":\"[2410.03457] CoCoLoFa: A Dataset of News Comments with Common Logical Fallacies Written by LLM-Assisted Crowds\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.03457\"},{\"title\":\"Paper page - Logical Fallacy Detection\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/papers/2202.13758\"},{\"title\":\"joey234/mmlu-logical_fallacies-original-neg · Datasets at Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/joey234/mmlu-logical_fallacies-original-neg\"},{\"title\":\"COCOLOFA: A Dataset of News Comments with Common ...\",\"url\":\"https://aclanthology.org/2024.emnlp-main.39.pdf\"},{\"title\":\"MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base · Datasets at Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base\"},{\"title\":\"CoCoLoFa: A Dataset of News Comments with Common Logical Fallacies Written by LLM-Assisted Crowds - ACL Anthology\",\"url\":\"https://aclanthology.org/2024.emnlp-main.39/\"}]\n\nHere's what I found about the **CoCoLoFa** dataset:\n\n## CoCoLoFa: A Dataset of News Comments with Common Logical Fallacies\n\nCoCoLoFa is a dataset introduced in the EMNLP 2024 long paper, \"CoCoLoFa: A Dataset of News Comments with Common Logical Fallacies Written by LLM-Assisted Crowds.\" This dataset is collected to enhance models' ability of identifying logical fallacies in online discussions.\n\n### Key Details\n\n- CoCoLoFa is the largest known logical fallacy dataset, containing 7,706 comments for 648 news articles, with each comment labeled for fallacy presence and type.\n- 143 crowd workers were recruited to write comments embodying specific fallacy types (e.g., slippery slope) in response to news articles, and an LLM-powered assistant was built into the workers' interface to aid in drafting and refining their comments.\n- CoCoLoFa considers eight types of logical fallacy, including appeal to authority, appeal to majority, appeal to nature, appeal to tradition, appeal to worse problems, false dilemma, hasty generalization, and slippery slope.\n\n### Performance\n\n- BERT-based models fine-tuned using CoCoLoFa achieved the highest fallacy detection (F1=0.86) and classification (F1=0.87) performance on its test set, outperforming the state-of-the-art LLMs.\n\n### Where to Access\n\n1. **GitHub**: The official repository is available at [https://github.com/Crowd-AI-Lab/cocolofa](https://github.com/Crowd-AI-Lab/cocolofa).\n2. **Hugging Face**: The paper page exists on Hugging Face at [https://huggingface.co/papers/2410.03457](https://huggingface.co/papers/2410.03457), though a dedicated Hugging Face dataset page does not appear to be linked yet.\n3. **arXiv**: The paper is available at [https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.03457](https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.03457).\n4. **ACL Anthology**: The paper was published in the Proceedings of the 2024 Conference on Empirical Methods in Natural Language Processing, Miami, Florida, USA, by the Association for Computational Linguistics.\n\n### Authors\nMin-Hsuan Yeh, Ruyuan Wan, and Ting-Hao Kenneth Huang.\n\n### Related Datasets on Hugging Face\n- **tasksource/logical-fallacy**: A dataset (Logic) of logical fallacies generally found in text, together with an additional challenge set for detecting logical fallacies in climate change claims (LogicClimate). Dataset and code are available at https://github.com/causalNLP/logical-fallacy.\n- **MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base**: A dataset produced for the purpose of enabling more accurate detection and handling of logical and other fallacies in LLMs.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"607fdfc9-907f-4bc3-829a-6743699977ac","uuid":"6f60bed3-b804-41f3-a0e0-2f0b3560e830","tool_use_result":{"query":"CoCoLoFa dataset download github huggingface logical fallacies","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01JtDca3g345MZK9LFBgsjDz","content":[{"title":"GitHub - Crowd-AI-Lab/cocolofa","url":"https://github.com/Crowd-AI-Lab/cocolofa"},{"title":"tasksource/logical-fallacy · Datasets at Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/datasets/tasksource/logical-fallacy"},{"title":"Paper page - CoCoLoFa: A Dataset of News Comments with Common Logical Fallacies Written by LLM-Assisted Crowds","url":"https://huggingface.co/papers/2410.03457"},{"title":"brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies · Datasets at Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/datasets/brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies"},{"title":"[2410.03457] CoCoLoFa: A Dataset of News Comments with Common Logical Fallacies Written by LLM-Assisted Crowds","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.03457"},{"title":"Paper page - Logical Fallacy Detection","url":"https://huggingface.co/papers/2202.13758"},{"title":"joey234/mmlu-logical_fallacies-original-neg · Datasets at Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/datasets/joey234/mmlu-logical_fallacies-original-neg"},{"title":"COCOLOFA: A Dataset of News Comments with Common ...","url":"https://aclanthology.org/2024.emnlp-main.39.pdf"},{"title":"MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base · Datasets at Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/datasets/MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base"},{"title":"CoCoLoFa: A Dataset of News Comments with Common Logical Fallacies Written by LLM-Assisted Crowds - ACL Anthology","url":"https://aclanthology.org/2024.emnlp-main.39/"}]},"Here's what I found about the **CoCoLoFa** dataset:\n\n## CoCoLoFa: A Dataset of News Comments with Common Logical Fallacies\n\nCoCoLoFa is a dataset introduced in the EMNLP 2024 long paper, \"CoCoLoFa: A Dataset of News Comments with Common Logical Fallacies Written by LLM-Assisted Crowds.\" This dataset is collected to enhance models' ability of identifying logical fallacies in online discussions.\n\n### Key Details\n\n- CoCoLoFa is the largest known logical fallacy dataset, containing 7,706 comments for 648 news articles, with each comment labeled for fallacy presence and type.\n- 143 crowd workers were recruited to write comments embodying specific fallacy types (e.g., slippery slope) in response to news articles, and an LLM-powered assistant was built into the workers' interface to aid in drafting and refining their comments.\n- CoCoLoFa considers eight types of logical fallacy, including appeal to authority, appeal to majority, appeal to nature, appeal to tradition, appeal to worse problems, false dilemma, hasty generalization, and slippery slope.\n\n### Performance\n\n- BERT-based models fine-tuned using CoCoLoFa achieved the highest fallacy detection (F1=0.86) and classification (F1=0.87) performance on its test set, outperforming the state-of-the-art LLMs.\n\n### Where to Access\n\n1. **GitHub**: The official repository is available at [https://github.com/Crowd-AI-Lab/cocolofa](https://github.com/Crowd-AI-Lab/cocolofa).\n2. **Hugging Face**: The paper page exists on Hugging Face at [https://huggingface.co/papers/2410.03457](https://huggingface.co/papers/2410.03457), though a dedicated Hugging Face dataset page does not appear to be linked yet.\n3. **arXiv**: The paper is available at [https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.03457](https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.03457).\n4. **ACL Anthology**: The paper was published in the Proceedings of the 2024 Conference on Empirical Methods in Natural Language Processing, Miami, Florida, USA, by the Association for Computational Linguistics.\n\n### Authors\nMin-Hsuan Yeh, Ruyuan Wan, and Ting-Hao Kenneth Huang.\n\n### Related Datasets on Hugging Face\n- **tasksource/logical-fallacy**: A dataset (Logic) of logical fallacies generally found in text, together with an additional challenge set for detecting logical fallacies in climate change claims (LogicClimate). Dataset and code are available at https://github.com/causalNLP/logical-fallacy.\n- **MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base**: A dataset produced for the purpose of enabling more accurate detection and handling of logical and other fallacies in LLMs."],"durationSeconds":18.663941729999962}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01G1t5qKcG7ZWnfNAPP81qkf","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"MAFALDA fallacy dataset github download huggingface\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"GitHub - ChadiHelwe/MAFALDA\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/ChadiHelwe/MAFALDA\"},{\"title\":\"MAFALDA | Pierre-Henri Paris\",\"url\":\"https://phparis.net/project/mafalda/\"},{\"title\":\"[2311.09761] MAFALDA: A Benchmark and Comprehensive Study of Fallacy Detection and Classification\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2311.09761\"},{\"title\":\"MAFALDA: A Benchmark and Comprehensive Study of Fallacy Detection and Classification - ACL Anthology\",\"url\":\"https://aclanthology.org/2024.naacl-long.270/\"},{\"title\":\"tasksource/logical-fallacy · Datasets at Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/tasksource/logical-fallacy\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - huggingface/datasets: 🤗 The largest hub of ready-to-use datasets for AI models with fast, easy-to-use and efficient data manipulation tools\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/huggingface/datasets\"},{\"title\":\"brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies · Datasets at Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - bodaay/HuggingFaceModelDownloader: Simple go utility to download HuggingFace Models and Datasets · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/bodaay/HuggingFaceModelDownloader\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - sisinflab-swot/mafalda: MAtchmaking Features for mAchine Learning Data Analysis\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/sisinflab-swot/mafalda\"},{\"title\":\"MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base · Datasets at Hugging Face\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/datasets/MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base\"}]\n\nHere are the results for your search on the **MAFALDA fallacy dataset**:\n\n## MAFALDA – GitHub Repository\n\nMAFALDA is a benchmark for fallacy classification that unites previous datasets. It comes with a taxonomy of fallacies that aligns, refines, and unifies previous classifications.\n\n- **GitHub**: [https://github.com/ChadiHelwe/MAFALDA](https://github.com/ChadiHelwe/MAFALDA)\n\n### Key Features:\n- It consolidates various datasets into a single, more comprehensive collection with a refined taxonomy that aligns, consolidates, and standardizes the classifications of fallacies.\n- The dataset includes detailed manual annotations for 200 texts, providing clear examples of various fallacies. Each annotation includes a manual explanation, which helps in understanding the rationale behind the classification.\n- Recognizing the subjective nature of fallacy identification, MAFALDA incorporates an annotation scheme that allows for multiple correct labels for certain fallacies, reflecting the real-world complexity of language and argumentation.\n- The benchmark evaluates several state-of-the-art language models under a zero-shot learning setting as well as human performance, providing insights into current capabilities and limitations in automatic fallacy detection.\n\n### Publication:\nChadi Helwe, Tom Calamai, Pierre-Henri Paris, Chloé Clavel, and Fabian Suchanek (2024). *MAFALDA: A Benchmark and Comprehensive Study of Fallacy Detection and Classification*. In Proceedings of the 2024 Conference of the North American Chapter of the Association for Computational Linguistics (NAACL), pages 4810–4845, Mexico City, Mexico.\n\n- **arXiv paper**: [https://arxiv.org/abs/2311.09761](https://arxiv.org/abs/2311.09761)\n- **ACL Anthology**: [https://aclanthology.org/2024.naacl-long.270/](https://aclanthology.org/2024.naacl-long.270/)\n\n---\n\n## Related Fallacy Datasets on Hugging Face\n\nWhile MAFALDA itself does not appear to have a dedicated Hugging Face page, here are related fallacy datasets available on Hugging Face:\n\n1. **`tasksource/logical-fallacy`** – Contains ~3.76k rows split into train (2.68k), test (511), and dev (570) sets, sourced from the causalNLP/logical-fallacy GitHub repository.\n   - [https://huggingface.co/datasets/tasksource/logical-fallacy](https://huggingface.co/datasets/tasksource/logical-fallacy)\n\n2. **`brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies`** – Available at [https://huggingface.co/datasets/brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies](https://huggingface.co/datasets/brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies)\n\n3. **`MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base`** – This dataset was produced for enabling more accurate detection and handling of logical and other fallacies in LLMs, with seed data taken from Wikipedia's list of Fallacies.\n   - [https://huggingface.co/datasets/MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base](https://huggingface.co/datasets/MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base)\n\nFor downloading the **MAFALDA dataset specifically**, the primary source is the [GitHub repository](https://github.com/ChadiHelwe/MAFALDA) by Chadi Helwe.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"607fdfc9-907f-4bc3-829a-6743699977ac","uuid":"1f337143-4ba9-4457-a249-3972f0716783","tool_use_result":{"query":"MAFALDA fallacy dataset github download huggingface","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01QLZGDZJ6hvH8SwGFF2tmqk","content":[{"title":"GitHub - ChadiHelwe/MAFALDA","url":"https://github.com/ChadiHelwe/MAFALDA"},{"title":"MAFALDA | Pierre-Henri Paris","url":"https://phparis.net/project/mafalda/"},{"title":"[2311.09761] MAFALDA: A Benchmark and Comprehensive Study of Fallacy Detection and Classification","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2311.09761"},{"title":"MAFALDA: A Benchmark and Comprehensive Study of Fallacy Detection and Classification - ACL Anthology","url":"https://aclanthology.org/2024.naacl-long.270/"},{"title":"tasksource/logical-fallacy · Datasets at Hugging Face","url":"https://huggingface.co/datasets/tasksource/logical-fallacy"},{"title":"GitHub - huggingface/datasets: 🤗 The largest hub of ready-to-use datasets for AI models with fast, easy-to-use and efficient data manipulatio