Helwe, Tom Calamai, Pierre-Henri Paris, Chloé Clavel, and Fabian Suchanek (2024). *MAFALDA: A Benchmark and Comprehensive Study of Fallacy Detection and Classification*. In Proceedings of the 2024 Conference of the North American Chapter of the Association for Computational Linguistics (NAACL), pages 4810–4845, Mexico City, Mexico.\n\n- **arXiv paper**: [https://arxiv.org/abs/2311.09761](https://arxiv.org/abs/2311.09761)\n- **ACL Anthology**: [https://aclanthology.org/2024.naacl-long.270/](https://aclanthology.org/2024.naacl-long.270/)\n\n---\n\n## Related Fallacy Datasets on Hugging Face\n\nWhile MAFALDA itself does not appear to have a dedicated Hugging Face page, here are related fallacy datasets available on Hugging Face:\n\n1. **`tasksource/logical-fallacy`** – Contains ~3.76k rows split into train (2.68k), test (511), and dev (570) sets, sourced from the causalNLP/logical-fallacy GitHub repository.\n   - [https://huggingface.co/datasets/tasksource/logical-fallacy](https://huggingface.co/datasets/tasksource/logical-fallacy)\n\n2. **`brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies`** – Available at [https://huggingface.co/datasets/brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies](https://huggingface.co/datasets/brucewlee1/mmlu-logical-fallacies)\n\n3. **`MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base`** – This dataset was produced for enabling more accurate detection and handling of logical and other fallacies in LLMs, with seed data taken from Wikipedia's list of Fallacies.\n   - [https://huggingface.co/datasets/MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base](https://huggingface.co/datasets/MrOvkill/fallacies-fallacy-base)\n\nFor downloading the **MAFALDA dataset specifically**, the primary source is the [GitHub repository](https://github.com/ChadiHelwe/MAFALDA) by Chadi Helwe."],"durationSeconds":23.892581204000045}}
