tent":"Read and extract key information from papers","status":"completed","activeForm":"Reading and extracting paper information"},{"content":"Find and download suitable datasets for fallacy detection experiments","status":"completed","activeForm":"Finding and downloading datasets"},{"content":"Search for relevant code repositories","status":"completed","activeForm":"Searching for code repositories"},{"content":"Create literature_review.md synthesis","status":"completed","activeForm":"Creating literature review"},{"content":"Create resources.md catalog","status":"completed","activeForm":"Creating resources catalog"},{"content":"Create completion marker","status":"completed","activeForm":"Creating completion marker"}],"verificationNudgeNeeded":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01CSydCuswMFgyzvdmLjfi4L","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Resource gathering is complete. Here's a summary of what was accomplished:\n\n## Summary\n\n### Papers (19 downloaded)\n- **6 core papers** on LLM fallacy detection (Pan 2024, Li 2024, Yeh 2024, Jin 2022, Helwe 2023, Sourati 2023)\n- **3 self-evaluation papers** directly relevant to the hypothesis (Tyen 2024 - \"LLMs cannot find reasoning errors\", Hong 2024 - \"Self-verification abilities\" with 232-type taxonomy, Liu 2023 - \"Self-contradictory reasoning\")\n- **10 additional papers** on CoT faithfulness, reasoning evaluation, and fallacy benchmarks\n\n### Datasets (8 downloaded)\n- **FALLACIES**: 4,640 steps, 232 fallacy types with hierarchical taxonomy - best for blindspot analysis\n- **LOGIC**: 3,761 examples, 13 types - standard benchmark\n- **BIG-Bench Mistake**: 2,186 CoT traces with error annotations - for step-level verification\n- **CoCoLoFa**: 7,706 comments, 8 types - ecologically valid\n- **MAFALDA**: 200 texts, 25 types - unified benchmark\n- **RuozhiBench**: 675 bilingual questions - misleading premise detection\n- **MMLU Logical Fallacies** and **LogicClimate** as supplementary\n\n### Code Repositories (7 cloned)\n- FALLACIES, MAFALDA, BIG-Bench-Mistake (evaluation frameworks)\n- causalNLP/logical-fallacy, USC logical-fallacy-identification (baselines)\n- CoCoLoFa, RuozhiBench (datasets with code)\n\n### Key Finding from Literature Review\nThe research gap is confirmed: **No existing work systematically compares self-evaluation vs cross-model evaluation for fallacy detection.** Tyen et al. (2024) explicitly call for this study, and Hong et al. (2024) demonstrate that fallacy detection performance is remarkably imbalanced across types - providing the foundation for blindspot analysis."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":353,"cache_read_input_tokens":130060,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":353,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"607fdfc9-907f-4bc3-829a-6743699977ac","uuid":"0ef53b7f-c738-45db-a69f-2b3bacd14c02"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":1321054,"duration_api_ms":1486535,"num_turns":84,"result":"Resource gathering is complete. Here's a summary of what was accomplished:\n\n## Summary\n\n### Papers (19 downloaded)\n- **6 core papers** on LLM fallacy detection (Pan 2024, Li 2024, Yeh 2024, Jin 2022, Helwe 2023, Sourati 2023)\n- **3 self-evaluation papers** directly relevant to the hypothesis (Tyen 2024 - \"LLMs cannot find reasoning errors\", Hong 2024 - \"Self-verification abilities\" with 232-type taxonomy, Liu 2023 - \"Self-contradictory reasoning\")\n- **10 additional papers** on CoT faithfulness, reasoning evaluation, and fallacy benchmarks\n\n### Datasets (8 downloaded)\n- **FALLACIES**: 4,640 steps, 232 fallacy types with hierarchical taxonomy - best for blindspot analysis\n- **LOGIC**: 3,761 examples, 13 types - standard benchmark\n- **BIG-Bench Mistake**: 2,186 CoT traces with error annotations - for step-level verification\n- **CoCoLoFa**: 7,706 comments, 8 types - ecologically valid\n- **MAFALDA**: 200 texts, 25 types - unified benchmark\n- **RuozhiBench**: 675 bilingual questions - misleading premise detection\n- **MMLU Logical Fallacies** and **LogicClimate** as supplementary\n\n### Code Repositories (7 cloned)\n- FALLACIES, MAFALDA, BIG-Bench-Mistake (evaluation frameworks)\n- causalNLP/logical-fallacy, USC logical-fallacy-identification (baselines)\n- CoCoLoFa, RuozhiBench (datasets with code)\n\n### Key Finding from Literature Review\nThe research gap is confirmed: **No existing work systematically compares self-evaluation vs cross-model evaluation for fallacy detection.** Tyen et al. (2024) explicitly call for this study, and Hong et al. (2024) demonstrate that fallacy detection performance is remarkably imbalanced across types - providing the foundation for blindspot analysis.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"607fdfc9-907f-4bc3-829a-6743699977ac","total_cost_usd":7.309323250000002,"usage":{"input_tokens":1416,"