{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01FomXsGYJobY1iHbjctzxxp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both background agents have completed. The fallacy detection papers agent uncovered an important additional finding:\n\n**Key insight from Sourati/Payandeh et al. (2023)**: GPT-4 is **69% more susceptible** to fallacious vs logical arguments - worse than GPT-3.5's 41%. And GPT-3.5 generates fallacies it cannot detect as a debater, demonstrating a **self-detection paradox** directly supporting our hypothesis.\n\n**From Richardson et al. (2025)**: More capable models produce more **human-like fallacies** (rho=0.360) while overall correctness shows **NO correlation** with capability (r=0.004). Scaling doesn't eliminate blindspots.\n\nLet me update the literature review with these critical findings."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2007,"cache_read_input_tokens":134691,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2007,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"607fdfc9-907f-4bc3-829a-6743699977ac","uuid":"b43ae0fc-6456-4103-8f17-4a5cc0d6e006"}
